## Latest session updates (2026-05-20)

Three substantive additions this session, documented in
\`theory/SESSION_2026_05_20.md\`:

1. **Empirical confirmation of φ = 1/2.** Re-analysis of the existing
   cloning aggregate with the theoretically motivated \`1/sqrt(L)\`
   extrapolation (because ν = 1/y_λ = 2 ⇒ Binder corrections go as
   L^{-1/2}) gives **φ = 0.502 ± 0.026, A = 0.96 ± 0.05**, replacing
   the previous biased \`1/L\`-extrapolation result of φ ≈ 0.43.
   Writeup: \`analysis/lambda_c_phi_analysis.md\`.

2. **NLSM theoretical framework added.** Adapted the Le Gal & Schirò
   replica Keldysh framework (arXiv:2511.22506, Nov 2025) to QJ-PPS,
   with ζ multiplying only the cross-replica vertex. Two model variants
   analysed:
   - **Case A** (two competing measurements, no Hamiltonian): D class,
     self-dual, λ_c = 1/2 ∀ ζ, Ising universality.
   - **Case B** (single measurement + free hopping, project's main
     model): DIII class, no self-duality, naive NLSM is incorrect at
     small ζ because the BdG localisation length ξ_ps ~ λ^{-2} replaces
     the dressed length as the relevant UV cutoff. Matching the NLSM
     cutoff to ξ_ps and running multicritical RG between a and ξ_ps
     **recovers λ_c ~ sqrt(ζ) from the NLSM framework itself**.

   Full derivation: \`theory/NLSM_FRAMEWORK.md\`.
   LaTeX writeup of the framework: \`~/Downloads/continuousmeasurements(2)/sections/sec8_replica_nlsm_pps.tex\`.

3. **Case A implementation spec written.** The current code only does
   Case B. Spec at \`theory/CASE_A_IMPLEMENTATION_SPEC.md\` gives a
   self-contained recipe for an implementation agent: 8 implementation
   steps + 7 validation gates + SLURM grid (260 jobs).

