- **Project**: \`ppsQJ_m2\` — measurement-induced phase transitions (MIPT) in
  a 1D Kitaev chain under quantum-jump partial postselection (QJ-PPS).
  Extends Kells–Meidan SciPost Phys 14, 3, 031 from diffusive to quantum-jump.
- **Repo**: \`github.com/ueborg/ppsQJ_m2\`. Local at \`/Users/catlover1337/Documents/ppsQJ_m2/\`.
- **Compute**: Habrok HPC (RUG), interactive nodes ~60 cores.
- **Language**: Python. Code uses numpy, scipy, tqdm; Gaussian fermionic backend.

## Model (Case B, current code)

Hamiltonian \$H = w \sum_j (c_j^\dagger c_{j+1} + \text{h.c.})\$ on \$L\$ sites.
Jump operators \$L_j = \sqrt{\alpha}\,d_j\$ with
\$d_j = (\gamma_{2j} - i\gamma_{2j+3})/2\$
(distance-3 Majorana bond operator).

Parametrization: \$\alpha + w = 1\$, \$\lambda := \alpha\$, \$\zeta \in [0, 1]\$
the postselection parameter. \$\zeta = 1\$ recovers Born-rule quantum jumps;
\$\zeta = 0\$ is full postselection (no clicks at all).

Trajectory measure is tilted by \$\zeta^{N_T}\$. The tilted Lindbladian
\$\mathcal{L}_\zeta[\rho] = -i[H,\rho] + \sum_j[\zeta J_j\rho J_j^\dagger - \tfrac{1}{2}\{J_j^\dagger J_j, \rho\}]
= \mathcal{L}_0 + \zeta \mathcal{J}\$
splits into no-click non-Hermitian piece \$\mathcal{L}_0\$ and click
recycling piece \$\zeta\mathcal{J}\$.

For Case A (the symmetry-protected variant analysed in
\`NLSM_FRAMEWORK.md\`), \$H = 0\$ and two measurement channels are
present with rates γ and α, parametrised as λ_A = α/(α+γ).

## Current top-level result

\$\boxed{\;\lambda_c(\zeta) \sim A\sqrt{\zeta}, \quad A = 0.96 \pm 0.05\;}\$

with two-parameter FSS structure
\$B_L(\lambda, \zeta) = \mathcal{B}(\lambda L^{1/2}, \zeta L, u L^{-\omega})\$,
i.e. \$y_\lambda = 1/2\$ from BdG localization, \$y_\zeta = 1\$ from
cross-Choi extensivity (\$\Delta_\zeta = 1\$).

**Confirmed this session** with proper 1/sqrt(L) Binder extrapolation:
φ = 0.502 ± 0.026 (matches predicted 1/2 to 1σ).

Born-rule endpoint \$\lambda_c(1) \approx 0.5\$ matches Carollo (PRA 2018).

Physical picture, now framed within the NLSM:
- Multicritical regime (small ζ): Gaussian fixed point at the origin
  + cross-Choi perturbation with \$\Delta_\zeta = 1\$. Criticality at
  \$\zeta \xi_{ps}(\lambda_c) \sim 1\$ with \$\xi_{ps} \sim \lambda^{-2}\$
  gives \$\lambda_c \sim \sqrt{\zeta}\$.
- DIII NLSM regime (ζ ~ 1): Lindbladian saddle dominant, bare coupling
  \$g_B \propto \zeta\lambda/(1-\lambda)\$, transition at \$g_B \approx 1\$,
  giving \$\lambda_c \to \lambda_{BR} \approx 0.5\$.
- Crossover at ζ ~ 0.25, consistent with the ζ = 0.5 outlier in data.

