## Eliminated scenarios

- **Scenario A** (\$\lambda_c \to 0.5\$ for all \$\zeta > 0\$, LMR-Ising
  persistence): RULED OUT by Binder data showing \$\lambda_c\$
  monotonically decreasing as \$\zeta \to 0\$.
- **Scenario B** (separatrix at \$\zeta_c \approx 0.143\$): ARTIFACT of
  c_eff threshold method; does not survive switch to Binder.
- **Original Scenario C** (linear \$\lambda_c \sim \zeta\$, φ = 1):
  EXCLUDED. Collapse residual 28% worse than \$\sqrt{\zeta}\$.

## Methodology lesson (still applies)

**c_eff method gives misleading results.** The c_eff = 1 threshold is
not a universal MIPT diagnostic. All extractions of \$\lambda_c\$ must
use **Binder cumulant crossings** with proper 1/sqrt(L) extrapolation.

When this session started, the most recent small-ζ runs on Habrok had
been analysed with the c_eff = 1 threshold, yielding φ = 0.201 (which
contradicts the 0.502 from Binder). This is the wrong method, NOT
a falsification of theory. **All new runs must store B_L_mean values
per (L, λ, ζ).**

