## Onboarding sequence for a fresh chat

1. Read this file (`HANDOFF.md`) end-to-end. ~3 minutes.
2. Read `theory/SESSION_2026_05_20.md`. ~3 minutes.
3. If working on theory: read `theory/NLSM_FRAMEWORK.md`. ~10 minutes.
4. If working on Case A numerics: read `theory/CASE_A_IMPLEMENTATION_SPEC.md`. ~10 minutes.
5. If working on Case B numerics: the recommended runs are in
   `SESSION_2026_05_20.md` §4, and the cloning entry points are in
   `pps_qj/cloning.py` + `scripts/`.

Do not re-derive things from scratch when an existing doc covers it.
If you disagree with something in an existing doc, *flag it* in a new
file rather than silently overwriting.

