## Things to NOT do silently

- Do not run any new numerics that store only c_eff. Always store B_L.
- Do not modify Case B code while implementing Case A — use parallel files.
- Do not "improve" the multicritical RG arguments — they're now grounded in
  the NLSM framework and any rederivation should reference NLSM_FRAMEWORK.md.
- Do not claim a numerical discrepancy with theory without verifying the
  analysis method first (e.g. c_eff vs Binder).
